But because of its position, okay,

254
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:57,720
the Levant is what we call a nothing part.

255
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,620
Or a meeting place.

256
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:05,240
So, every culture, every language,

257
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:06,820
every religion that

258
00:15:06,820 --> 00:15:10,480
was imaginable at this
time met in the Levant.

259
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:15,160
Okay? Mainly for trade purposes.

260
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:19,080
Right? Because, again, Egypt and
Mesopotamia are extremely wealthy.

261
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:24,520
The Levant, you can go across the
Mediterranean into all of Europe

262
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:25,860
and into Northern Africa.

263
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:30,600
Okay? So, the Levant was really the
center of the world for the Hittites.

264
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:34,420
For most of its history. And so, it was
a meeting place, mainly for traders.

265
00:15:35,540 --> 00:15:37,660
Right? At this time,

266
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,400
Levant was divided into
different sections.

267
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:45,080
A province called Canine
was a province of Egypt.

268
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:49,960
And Canine was special to Egypt
because the Egyptians loved two things.

269
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:52,300
They loved wine. They loved olive oil.

270
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:57,420
And the Levant was very good
at harvesting both wine,

271
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:59,880
good wine, and olive oil.

272
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:02,240
So, but

273
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:06,540
the Egyptians didn't really
like to go outside Egypt.

274
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:12,560
So, the people administrating the
Levant were local elites tied to Egypt,

275
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:13,960
but also foreign mercenaries.

276
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:18,100
And these foreign mercenaries
were from as far as Greece.

277
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,120
Okay? And we know this because

278
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:23,780
we've discovered Greek pottery

279
00:16:23,780 --> 00:16:26,300
that dates back to this period.

280
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,580
Okay? These foreign mercenaries would then

281
00:16:29,580 --> 00:16:31,620
intermarry with the local women.

282
00:16:31,780 --> 00:16:35,580
Because as you can imagine,
these are young males.

283
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:40,420
Okay? You also had lots

284
00:16:40,420 --> 00:16:45,320
of nomads living in the Levant

285
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,740
because of Arabia.

286
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:48,680
Right? Okay?

287
00:16:49,060 --> 00:16:52,120
Lots of nomads. People
we call the Bedouins.

288
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:57,220
You also had people living in the hills.

289
00:16:57,220 --> 00:17:01,320
All of the Levant, the hill people.

290
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:04,160
And you have these cities. Okay?

291
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:10,140
The Canaanites. You also
had, believe it or not,

292
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:12,800
Egyptian priests living in this area.

293
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:14,620
Why would they live in this area?

294
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:18,020
Well, because they had a certain religion

295
00:17:18,020 --> 00:17:19,580
that

296
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:23,840
was considered heretical
or controversial in Egypt.

297
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:25,260
So they had to leave to
practice their religion.

298
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:27,200
Or maybe they were a
little bit more religious.

299
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,760
Or maybe they were priests who
got into a political struggle.

300
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:33,320
And as such, they were
exiled to the Levant.

301
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:36,760
Okay? So, does that make sense?

302
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:41,680
The Levant, it's not
at this point a nation.

303
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:44,800
At this point, it's
really a meeting place.

304
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,900
A melting pot of cultures,

305
00:17:48,060 --> 00:17:49,920
languages, and religions.

306
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:52,120
It's as diverse as can be.

307
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:55,580
And historically, this has
always been the case. Right?

308
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:03,060
Then, what happened, of course,

309
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:06,880
is the Bronze Age collapse.

310
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:10,260
The thing about the Bronze
Age collapse is you

311
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:13,840
have this massive migration
of people looking for food.

312
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:16,420
Right? These are called the Sea Peoples.

313
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,520
They're basically like pirates. And

314
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:25,140
there are these massive waves of
Sea People attacking the Hittites.

315
00:18:25,140 --> 00:18:27,060
Attacking the Levant and attacking Egypt.

316
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:29,580
And again, these are like refugees. Okay?

317
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,040
This is a forced migration.

318
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,860
And they're trying to feed their families.

319
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:38,260
They basically overrun the Hittites.

320
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,360
They destroy the cities of the Levant.

321
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:44,300
And they almost destroy Egypt.

322
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,960
But Egypt, because it's so wealthy,

323
00:18:46,260 --> 00:18:49,840
it's able to hold off the Sea People.

324
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:54,040
Eventually, what happens
is, the Sea Peoples

325
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,900
and Egypt come to an agreement and say,

326
00:18:57,080 --> 00:19:00,680
Listen, stop attacking us and
we'll give you land in the Levant.

327
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:01,980
You can settle down there.

328
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:03,540
You can grow your own food.

329
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:05,800
You can feed your families. Okay?

330
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:10,220
And this place is what we call Philistia.

331
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:13,660
And these people are
called the Philistines.

332
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:17,560
So these are basically the Sea Peoples.

333
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:19,120
Mainly Greek, actually.

334
00:19:19,320 --> 00:19:21,560
There are a lot of Greeks
among the Philistines.

335
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:28,280
But this creates a problem
for everyone in the Levant.

336
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:32,140
Because now you have a foreign presence

337
00:19:32,140 --> 00:19:35,080
that

338
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:37,200
is very aggressive and expansionist.

339
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,500
Okay? So now,

340
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:43,140
the people in the Levant
need to come together

341
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:47,060
and fend off this threat
from the Philistines.

342
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:49,800
They also have these neighbors as well.

343
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,540
These other cultures. These other people.

344
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:52,820
They keep on attacking them. Okay?

345
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:55,300
So these are extremely diverse people.

346
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:57,000
And so

347
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,960
what they agree to do is elect a

348
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:04,020
king to lead them in war
against the Philistines.

349
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:08,620
And this person is named Saul. King Saul.

350
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:17,540
Alright? And King Saul
is a very good king.

351
00:20:17,660 --> 00:20:21,020
He's a very good military
leader. He's helping the people.

352
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:25,520
He's helping the people in the Levant fend
off the Philistines and aggressive neighbors.

353
00:20:26,060 --> 00:20:28,360
Okay? So this is a military alliance.

354
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:33,720
King Saul employs a lot of mercenaries.

355
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:39,660
And one of these mercenaries
is named David. David.

356
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:46,380
David is an extremely capable,

357
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:49,020
charismatic soldier.

358
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:51,620
Who develops a following.

359
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,980
David, as you can imagine,
because he's very charismatic,

360
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:57,780
is also very ambitious.

361
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:01,120
And eventually, he has
a falling out with Saul.

362
00:21:01,380 --> 00:21:04,440
Okay? David is Saul's best
general, best soldier.

363
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:06,100
But David is too ambitious.

364
00:21:06,380 --> 00:21:08,160
And Saul sort of suspects David.

365
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:12,340
So what David does is he runs off

366
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:14,280
and joins the Philistines.

367
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:18,840
Okay? He's not fighting
for the Philistines.

368
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:22,020
What's really important
for us to understand,

369
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:24,200
and I know it's a hard concept.

370
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:27,840
But borders and alliances

371
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:31,840
and allegiances are
extremely fluid at this time.

372
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:35,060
If it benefits me, I'll fight for you.

373
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:37,660
But if it doesn't benefit
me, then I'll betray you.

374
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:42,060
Okay? There are different
factions within all alliances.

375
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:46,440
Okay? So the Philistines are divided
among different ethnic groups.

376
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:48,820
The people in the Levant are divided.

377
00:21:48,820 --> 00:21:50,960
The people in the Levant are divided
into different political factions.

378
00:21:51,220 --> 00:21:53,440
You have these hill people.
You have these nomads.

379
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:55,760
You have these foreign mercenaries.

380
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,280
And they're fighting
for different reasons.

381
00:21:57,660 --> 00:21:59,540
So these alliances are always shifting.

382
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:04,320
Okay? So David goes off and
fights for the Philistines.

383
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:08,660
King Saul and his sons are
eventually killed in battle.

384
00:22:09,220 --> 00:22:12,120
And David sees a political opening.

385
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:15,980
So he turns back into Levant.

386
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:20,340
And he starts to politically
maneuver to be the new king.

387
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:24,540
Okay? And

388
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:27,840
his power base is in
a place called Hebron,

389
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:30,140
or in south the Levant.

390
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:33,320
But the house of Saul is still around.

391
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,400
And so there's a civil war now going on.

392
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,880
And eventually David triumphs.

393
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:43,760
And then David's able
to unite these people.

394
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:45,960
And he creates a new nation
called the Philistines.

395
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:48,500
Israel. All right?

396
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:53,720
And then Israel is able,
under David's leadership,

397
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:55,780
is able to

398
00:22:55,780 --> 00:23:01,200
basically put down

399
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,660
any aggressions from its neighbors.

400
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:07,320
And they're able to build an empire.

401
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:09,140
A small empire. Okay?

402
00:23:09,220 --> 00:23:10,600
Nowhere near Egypt.

403
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:13,860
But it's an empire. All right?

404
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:19,600
So. This is what we know from
the archeological record.

405
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:25,040
But David is so charismatic that

406
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:29,780
when he dies, his son Solomon is not
able to hold the empire together.

407
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:34,640
So what happens is Israel

408
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:37,720
divides into the northern kingdom

409
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:39,900
and Judah.

410
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:43,260
Which is where the house of David is.

411
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:45,780
Okay? Now again,

412
00:23:45,940 --> 00:23:50,440
the Levant is a very
important strategic location.

413
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:54,180
So as these empires,

414
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:57,840
major empires, start to
consolidate the power,

415
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,640
they want to take over the Levant.

416
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:05,080
Okay? So the Assyrian Empire comes in

417
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,660
and destroys the northern kingdom.

418
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:08,900
And then

419
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:14,280
eventually the Babylonian
Empire will come in.

420
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:15,640
And destroy Judah.

421
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:20,340
Okay? The Babylonians will
take the Israel elite.

422
00:24:20,540 --> 00:24:22,180
Basically the royalty.

423
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,940
And force them to go to Babylon.

424
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:27,100
Where they will be held as hostages.

425
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:32,100
Or captives. Eventually,

426
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:38,020
what will happen next is
the Persian Empire will come

427
00:24:38,020 --> 00:24:42,300
and defeat Babylon.

428
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:45,660
And what they do next is very interesting.

429
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:49,280
They decide they will

430
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:52,600
release these Israelite elite.

431
00:24:53,580 --> 00:24:57,760
Have them return to Jerusalem and Israel.

432
00:24:58,020 --> 00:25:00,980
And have them govern the Levant.

433
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:06,800
Based on. And have them govern the Levant.

434
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:08,900
Okay? Does that make sense? And

435
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:12,280
it is only at this point
that we get the term Babylon.

436
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:14,660
And the Jews. Okay?

437
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:16,000
This is a Persian idea.

438
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,220
The Jews. Before they were
called the Israelites.

439
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:22,660
And this is about 500 BC.

440
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:25,200
Okay? 500 BC. And

441
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:29,920
now we have a radical
departure from the tradition.

442
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:33,520
Okay? And so I'll explain
three major differences.

443
00:25:35,060 --> 00:25:39,200
And then I'll explain, I'll go into detail
about these differences in future classes.

444
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:45,100
Okay? The first major
difference is Israel.

445
00:25:46,060 --> 00:25:49,620
Under the Israelites. It's
a polytheistic religion.

446
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:54,300
They have one god, Yahweh.

447
00:25:54,540 --> 00:25:58,180
But Yahweh. But they also
have a pantheon of gods.

448
00:25:58,420 --> 00:26:01,240
Which is the same. Which is
true for every other religion.

449
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,960
Right? There's a pantheon of
gods. Yahweh is at the top.

450
00:26:04,180 --> 00:26:06,060
But they also celebrate other gods.

451
00:26:06,140 --> 00:26:08,220
Like Baal and Asherah.

452
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:10,160
Okay? We know because they're
written down in the Bible.

453
00:26:10,460 --> 00:26:15,340
So we know at this point, Israel is
still a polytheistic religion. But

454
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:21,120
after the Persian Empire
returns them to Judaism,

455
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:24,260
they became a monotheistic religion.

456
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:28,140
Or the beginnings of a
monotheistic religion.

457
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:32,480
Why? Because when

458
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:37,360
the Jews are released from
captivity by the Persians.

459
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:40,620
Their religion merges with

460
00:26:40,620 --> 00:26:43,380
that of the Persian religion
called Zoroastrianism.

461
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:46,300
And Zoroastrianism is
a dualistic religion.

462
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:48,360
Okay? Meaning there's good and evil.

463
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:51,680
So that's the first major difference.

464
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,520
At the beginning,

465
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:58,640
the Bible was very much
a polytheistic religion.

466
00:26:58,980 --> 00:27:02,840
And then after the
Israelites became the Jews,

467
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:06,720
it became monotheistic.

468
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:10,000
Okay? Second big difference is this.

469
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:12,600
Second big difference is during this time,

470
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:15,180
the people with the power
in Israel were the kings.

471
00:27:15,580 --> 00:27:18,900
Okay? The monarchy. But

472
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:24,760
after 500 BCE,

473
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:27,640
the Jews decided they
didn't want any kings.

474
00:27:27,860 --> 00:27:31,200
And they couldn't have kings because
their overlords are the Persians.

475
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:34,860
Right? So the center of
power became the priesthood.

476
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:37,580
Okay? The priests.

477
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:42,780
The people with the absolute
authority are the priests,

478
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,140
not the kings.

479
00:27:44,780 --> 00:27:48,620
There are kings, but the kings
are not subservient to the priests

480
00:27:48,620 --> 00:27:51,180
who speak on behalf of Yahweh.

481
00:27:52,460 --> 00:27:55,060
Okay? Because now it's
a monotheistic religion.

482
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:00,260
And then there's one other difference.

483
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:02,640
The other difference is, remember,

484
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:05,820
at this point they're
polytheistic and they're kings.

485
00:28:05,820 --> 00:28:09,000
Okay? Which means they are tolerant.

486
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:14,680
They're welcoming of
other religions, right?

487
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:17,640
Because you're polytheistic.
But also, as kings,

488
00:28:17,820 --> 00:28:21,760
you need to establish diplomatic
alliances with other countries,

489
00:28:21,860 --> 00:28:23,780
who have different religions. Right?

490
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:29,600
So when you marry someone from
another political dynasty,

491
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:31,780
you also are marrying into that religion.

492
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:36,140
Does that make sense? So
Israel, under the kings,

493
00:28:36,260 --> 00:28:37,760
is a very tolerant religion.

494
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:41,000
But if you're run by priests,

495
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,760
right, you become intolerant.

496
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:48,720
Because you insist that
your religion is the best.

497
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:53,440
Okay? And

498
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:57,080
that's why, after the
Persians lost control,

499
00:28:57,140 --> 00:29:00,600
and the Greeks came in to the Levant,

500
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:03,480
this is the Seleucid Empire.

501
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:07,240
Okay? The Jews rebelled
against the Greeks.

502
00:29:07,380 --> 00:29:11,660
Because the Greeks were polytheistic, and
the Jews considered themselves monotheistic.

503
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:15,640
Okay? They refused to
acknowledge the culture

504
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:16,900
and the religion of the Greeks.

505
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:20,840
And then things got really
bad when the Romans came in.

506
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:23,140
Okay? Does that make sense?

507
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:31,920
Okay, so this is the history
of the Jewish people.

508
00:29:32,580 --> 00:29:35,100
Up until the birth of Jesus.

